Preheat #oven{} to 400 degrees. (TIP: If you have a toaster oven, feel free to
skip preheating.) Wash and dry produce.

Trim and peel @carrot{3%ounce}; grate on the largest holes of a #box
grater{} over a #medium bowl{}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating
whites from greens.

Thinly slice @fully cooked chicken breasts{9%ounce} crosswise.

== Creamy Slaw ==

To bowl with carrot, add @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}, scallion greens,
@sour cream{4%tablespoon}, @white wine vinegar{2%teaspoon}, and
@sugar{1.5%teaspoon}. Season with a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{}; toss to combine.

== Toast the Buns ==

Halve @brioche buns{2}. Toast cut sides up directly on oven rack (or in a
#toaster oven{}) until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Buffalo Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat.
Add scallion whites; cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @Frank's seasoning blend{7.2%g}, @Frank's Red Hot Sauce{3}, and
@butter{2%tablespoon}; cook, stirring, until butter has melted.

Add chicken and cook, stirring, until chicken is warmed through,
~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Fill buns with buffalo chicken and a bit of creamy slaw if desired; drizzle with
@buttermilk ranch dressing{1.5%ounce}.

Divide sandos between plates and serve with remaining creamy slaw on the side.

> When you mix spicy buffalo sauce with cooling ranch dressing, there's almost
no better flavor combination. Plus, why just drizzle creamy dressing on your
sando when you can have a creamy slaw on the side, too?